j. SalesLoft, Inc.
This website also uses tracking software from SalesLoft, Inc. (3423 Piedmont Road Northeast Suite 321 Atlanta, GA 30305) to collect information about the use of our website to optimize the website for our visitors. SalesLoft collects information that your browser sends whenever you visit our website. This data may include information such as your computer’s Internet Protocol (“IP”) address, browser type, browser version, the pages of our Services that you visit, the time and date of your visit, the time you spent on those pages, and other statistics. For further information regarding SalesLoft, visit their privacy policy
https://salesloft.com/platform-privacy-notice/
.
k. Quora
Foxit uses the Quora Pixel from Quora (Quora, Inc. 650 Castro St 450, Mountain View, CA 94041, USA). The Quora Pixel is a tool that is placed in our website to track traffic and conversions of website visitors coming to Foxit.com from the Quora website. When someone clicks on our ad and lands our website, the Quora Pixel allows us to identify how many people are visiting our website and what actions they are taking. For more information about Quora, visit
https://www.quora.com/about/privacy
.
l. Demandbase
Our website uses Demandbase. Demandbase uses cookies and web beacons, such as invisible tracking pixels, to collect non-personal information (browser version, operating system, IP address, cookie information, timestamp). Foxit collects corporate and other firmographic information related to your IP address. The cookies are readable only by Demandbase, with identifiers that may be linked to certain non-personal information or non-personal third party advertising IDs. For more information, please see
https://www.demandbase.com/privacy-policy/
.
m. Mailgun Technologies, Inc.
Some Foxit cloud services use Mailgun email services from Mailgun Technologies, Inc. (“Mailgun”) to send emails on behalf of Foxit and to deliver the service and account management notice to You. Mailgun collects information that your browser sends whenever you fill in a sign up or contact form on their website or send Foxit an email. This data may include Your personal information (i.e., Your name, company name, email address) and your non-personal information. For further information regarding Mailgun, visit their privacy policy
https://www.mailgun.com/privacy-policy
.
n. Third Party Cloud Storage Services
We may provide third party cloud storage services in our products and services for your convenience at your choice, such as Google Drive, Microsoft OneDrive, Dropbox, or others to you. You acknowledge and understand that the data collection of such cloud storage services shall be governed by the privacy policy provided by such third parties.
o. Foxit Dashboard
For the purpose of improving product quality and features, we may process how you use some of our products and services (“Usage Data”) with our internal system Foxit Dashboard. You have the option to share the following data about how you use and interact Foxit products and services:
System information, such as UUID, devices, operating system (version, language);
Foxit product information, such as product name, version, language;
Information about your documents, such as number of pages, and unique document identifiers, (but not the content in your documents);
Document usage information such as how many times you open a document; and
How you interact with Foxit’s products and services, including the features you use and the options you select.
You can choose not to share Usage Data by setting your preferences on your products or services page.
p. Gartner
Foxit uses the Gartner tracking tag from Gartner Digital Markets (Gartner, Inc. 56 Top Gallant Road Stamford, CT 06902 USA). The Gartner tracking tag is placed in our website to track traffic and conversions of website visitors coming to Foxit.com from the Gartner family of brands including Capterra, GetApp, and Software Advice. When someone clicks on our ad and lands on our website, the Gartner tag allows us to identify how many people are visiting our website and what actions they are taking. For more information about Gartner, visit
https://www.gartner.com/en
.
