r. Azure AI Services
Some Foxit products/services use Azure AI services from Microsoft (Microsoft Corporation, One Microsoft Way Redmond, WA 98052-6399, USA).
Azure Open AI
The AI Assistant feature is placed in our products/services to help you to summarize and rewrite the content you choose and also extract key/value information from your documents. You acknowledge and agree that Microsoft will process the text prompts, queries and responses. Visit
Data, privacy, and security for Azure OpenAI Service - Azure AI services | Microsoft Learn
for more information.
Azure AI Document Intelligence
Your use of AI Assistant feature will entail your data being uploaded onto Azure Storage and processed by Microsoft; such data and extracted results will be temporarily stored in Azure Storage in the same region as the request and will be deleted within 24 hours. Visit
Data, privacy, and security for Document Intelligence - Azure AI services | Microsoft Learn
.
Text to Speech
Foxit uses Text to Speech to process certain user input to generate audio output. These inputs are temporarily processed by Microsoft but will not be retained or stored in Azure storage once the processing is complete. No personal data will be permanently stored or accessible by Microsoft during this process. Visit
Data, privacy, and security for text to speech - Azure AI services | Microsoft Learn
for more information.
