8. CALIFORNIA PRIVACY RIGHTS
The California Consumer Privacy Act (“
CCPA
”) provides certain legal rights for California residents. This section generally describes those rights and how you may exercise them in connection with our practices described in this policy.
6sense has disclosed Personal Information in the categories identified in Section 2 to its vendors and service providers in the last 12 months for the purposes described in Section 4, including to provide services to our Subscribers or for operational and other purposes as permitted in our agreements with Subscribers and as provided in this Privacy Policy.
Disclosure and Sale or Share of Personal Information and the Right to Opt-Out
Sale of Business Profile Information
As an optional feature of 6sense services, we compile Business Profile Information and make this data available in our Business Database to our Subscriber customers and partners for their business purposes. Under our current subscriptions, we do not add Subscriber-Provided Information to our Business Database.
Business Profile Information may contain information about individuals’ business personas including name, employer, job title, email address, phone number, office address, and work or educational history.
If you would like to opt-out of the sale of your Personal Information that might be included within the Business Database, please click here:
Do Not Sell or Share My Personal Information
We make Personal Information in our Business Database available on a subscription basis. Sales are made to partners or Subscribers to sales or marketing teams in B2B companies that are looking to establish a connection with or gain insights into potential buyers of their offerings. In the past twelve (12) months, we’ve sold the following categories of business-related Personal Information in the Business Database:
Identifiers
, like your name or username, business email address, business title, company, location, business phone number, IP address, account ID, device ID, cookie ID, and other similar identifiers.
Commercial Information
: Information related to purchases that you might make in a business context.
Electronic, visual, or similar information
, such as your profile photo.
Professional or Employment-Related Information
: Information related to your employment, including current job title, and work history.
Inferences drawn from any of the above
: Business-related information we can determine or estimate about you based on the Business Profile Information.
We do not disclose, sell, collect, retain, or share sensitive personal information (which is personal information that is not publicly available like your Social Security number, driver’s license number, or medical history.) The identified categories of Business Profile Information that are disclosed and/or sold by 6sense to its Subscribers include business contact information in the context of an employee’s role with their employer. We do not sell or share the Personal Information of consumers under 16 years of age.
Share of Personal Information by 6sense for Advertising Purposes
6sense may use your Personal Information for advertising purposes on behalf of itself or its Subscribers. With respect to visitors to the 6sense website, 6sense may use information learned from a retargeting cookie placed by 6sense on your browser that allows 6sense to display ads to you on other wesbites, based on your visit to the 6sense website. If you would like to opt-out of the share of your Personal Information used to show ads to you on other sites, please click here to opt out:
Do Not Sell or Share My Personal Information
In the past twelve (12) months, we’ve shared the following categories of Personal Information with our service providers and business partners for advertising purposes:
Identifiers
, like your email address, IP address, account ID, device ID, cookie ID, and other similar identifiers.
Commercial Information
: Information related to purchases that you might make in a business context.
Internet or other electronic network activity information
, including but not limited to, browsing history and website activity.
Inferences drawn from any of the above
: Business-related information we can determine or estimate about you based on your Personal Information.
Examples: Purchase preferences in connection with your employment, potential future purchase behavior in connection with your employment.
We do not disclose, sell, collect, retain, or share sensitive personal information (which is personal information that is not publicly available like your Social Security number, driver’s license number, or medical history.) We do not sell or share the Personal Information of consumers under 16 years of age.
Your Rights.
If you are a California resident, you have the right to:
Opt-Out of the Sale and Share of Your Data.
You can request that we do not sell or share Personal Information about you. Once we receive and verify your request, we will not sell or share your Personal Information. You can opt-out of the sale of your data
here.
Access.
You can request that we disclose certain information to you about our collection and use of your Personal Information in the past 12 months with respect to our role as a “business” under the CCPA. Once we receive and verify your request, we will give you the following information:
The categories of Personal Information we collected about you.
The categories of sources of Personal Information we collected about you.
Our business or commercial purpose for collecting or selling that Personal Information.
The categories of third parties with whom we share that Personal Information.
The specific pieces of Personal Information we collected about you.
Delete.
You can request that we delete the Personal Information that we collected from you. Once we receive and verify your request, we will delete your Personal Information from our records. We are not required to delete information if we need to use it for the following:
Completing a transaction or contract with you.
Detecting security interests, protecting against malicious, deceptive, fraudulent, or illegal activity, or prosecuting people responsible for that activity.
Debugging our products to identify and repair errors to our Services.
Exercising, and allowing others to exercise, free speech, or other legal rights.
Internal uses that align with your expectations.
Complying with a legal requirement.
Other internal and lawful uses consistent with the reasons you provided the information.
Non-Discrimination.
We will not discriminate against you for exercising any of your CCPA rights.
Exercising Rights.
To exercise the above rights, please visit our
Privacy Center
,
or send a letter or email with your request and current contact information to 6sense at:
6Sense Insights, Inc.
450 Mission Street, Suite 201
San Francisco, CA 94105
Or Email:
DataSubjectRequests@6sense.com
In order to protect your privacy, we will ask you to verify your identity before we can act on your access or deletion request. This process may require you to provide additional information, which we will only use for verification purposes.
Agent Requests.
You may authorize someone to make a privacy rights request on your behalf (an authorized agent). Authorized agents will need to demonstrate that you’ve authorized them to act on your behalf, and that they are registered with the California Secretary of State to conduct business in California, or must demonstrate they have power of attorney pursuant to applicable probate law. We retain the right to request confirmation directly from you confirming that the agent is authorized to make such a request, or to request additional information to confirm the agent’s identity. An authorized agent is prohibited from using a consumer’s personal information, or any information collected from or about the consumer, for any purpose other than to fulfill the consumer’s requests, for verification, or for fraud prevention.
